 The PDP governorship flagbearer in Enugu State, Mr. Peter Ndubuisi Mbah has disclosed his plan to move the economy of the state from N4.4bn to N30bn, if elected governor in the forthcoming 2023 general election. Mbah who is the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Pinnacle Oil and Gas Ltd, a leading company in the downstream sector in an interview said he envisions an Enugu State that is going to be one of the top three states in Nigeria as he aims to achieve a zero per cent rate in poverty headcount index. The PDP candidate said that he is driven by a vision and mission to deliver a quality people-focused government and to make Enugu State the preferred destination for investment, business, tourism and living.